               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the ruling King; headings and incipits of the constituent texts; directives for the ministers; some of the musical notation signs above the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of decorated quire marks; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numbers.&#xD;
&#xD;
The incipit pages of most of the constituent texts are written alternately in red and black lines (s. fols. 5r, 29r, 50v, 61rb, 64v, 75r, etc.).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Liturgical indications (directives) concerning particular Anaphoras are written partly in Gǝʿǝz, partly in Amharic (s. fols. 111rb, 118rb, etc.).</note>
                  </msItem>
